<h2>Dragging Groups</h2>
<h3>Drag with Certain Items</h3>
<p>
    Elements can be set to only drag with certain items.
</p>
<div id="box">
    <div moveit-item class="card">1</div>
    <div moveit-item class="card">2</div>
    <div moveit-item class="card">3</div>
    <div moveit-item class="card">4</div>
    <div moveit-item class="card">5</div>
    <div moveit-item class="card">6</div>
</div>
<p>
    In this example, items can only be swapped with numbers that are less than it. Notice that "1" cannot be dragged.
</p>
<div class="example">
    <h3>JavaScript</h3>
    <pre>
moveIt.setDraggableWith([0,1,2,3,4,5], []);
moveIt.addDraggableWith([1,2,3,4,5], [0]);
moveIt.addDraggableWith([2,3,4,5], [1]);
moveIt.addDraggableWith([3,4,5], [2]);
moveIt.addDraggableWith([4,5], [3]);
moveIt.addDraggableWith([5], [4]);
    </pre>
</div>
<b>Warning</b>
<p>
    If the element used for <code style="font-size: 12pt;">moveIt.elementHover</code> is a different size than the original item,
    it could cause hovering inaccuracy.
</p>
<h3>Subgroups</h3>
<div id="box">
    <div moveit-item class="card">1</div>
    <div moveit-item class="card">2</div>
    <div moveit-item class="card">3</div>
    <div moveit-item class="card">4</div>
    <div moveit-item class="card">5</div>
    <div moveit-item class="card">6</div>
</div>
<p>
    In this example, items labelled with even numbers can only be swapped with even numbers and odd with odd.
</p>
<div class="example">
    <h3>JavaScript</h3>
    <pre>
moveIt.setDraggableWith([0,2,4], [0,2,4]);
moveIt.setDraggableWith([1,3,5], [1,3,5]);
    </pre>
</div>